HEADWORD: Patesi
<hw>Pa*te"si</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Assyrian.]</ety>
<fld>(Babylonian Antiq.)</fld> <def>A religious as well as a secular
designation applied to rulers of some of the city states of ancient
Chaldea, as Lagash or Shirpurla, who were conceived to be direct
representatives of the tutelary god of the place.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

